technologies.name: Magento
technologies.description: Magento is an open-source ecommerce platform written in PHP.

technologies.name: Algolia
technologies.description: Algolia offers a hosted web search product delivering real-time results.

technologies.name: Node.js
technologies.description: Node.js is an open-source, cross-platform, JavaScript runtime environment that executes JavaScript code outside a web browser.

technologies.name: MySQL
technologies.description: MySQL is an open-source relational database management system.

technologies.name: PHP
technologies.description: PHP is a general-purpose scripting language used for web development.

technologies.name: Vue.js
technologies.description: Vue.js is an open-source modelviewviewmodel JavaScript framework for building user interfaces and single-page applications.

technologies.name: Nuxt.js
technologies.description: Nuxt is a Vue framework for developing modern web applications.

technologies.name: Google Tag Manager
technologies.description: Google Tag Manager is a tag management system (TMS) that allows you to quickly and easily update measurement codes and related code fragments collectively known as tags on your website or mobile app.

technologies.name: Lodash
technologies.description: Lodash is a JavaScript library which provides utility functions for common programming tasks using the functional programming paradigm.

technologies.name: core-js
technologies.description: core-js is a modular standard library for JavaScript, with polyfills for cutting-edge ECMAScript features.

technologies.name: Cookiebot
technologies.description: Cookiebot is a cloud-driven solution that automatically controls cookies and trackers, enabling full GDPR/ePrivacy and CCPA compliance for websites.

technologies.name: Google Font API
technologies.description: Google Font API is a web service that supports open-source font files that can be used on your web designs.

technologies.name: DigitalOcean Spaces
technologies.description: DigitalOcean Spaces is a cloud-based object storage service provided by DigitalOcean, a cloud infrastructure provider. It allows users to store and retrieve large amounts of data, such as images, videos, audio files, backups, and logs, using a simple RESTful API or a web-based graphical user interface (GUI).

technologies.name: HSTS
technologies.description: HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) informs browsers that the site should only be accessed using HTTPS.

technologies.name: Webpack
technologies.description: Webpack is an open-source JavaScript module bundler.

technologies.name: Open Graph
technologies.description: Open Graph is a protocol that is used to integrate any web page into the social graph.

accessibility.title: Accessibility
accessibility.description: These checks highlight opportunities to [improve the accessibility of your web app](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/accessibility/). Only a subset of accessibility issues can be automatically detected so manual testing is also encouraged.
accessibility.manualDescription: These items address areas which an automated testing tool cannot cover. Learn more in our guide on [conducting an accessibility review](https://web.dev/how-to-review/).

seo.title: SEO
seo.description: These checks ensure that your page is following basic search engine optimization advice. There are many additional factors Lighthouse does not score here that may affect your search ranking, including performance on [Core Web Vitals](https://web.dev/learn-core-web-vitals/). [Learn more about Google Search Essentials](https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/35769).
seo.manualDescription: Run these additional validators on your site to check additional SEO best practices.

pwa.title: PWA
pwa.description: These checks validate the aspects of a Progressive Web App. [Learn what makes a good Progressive Web App](https://web.dev/pwa-checklist/).
pwa.manualDescription: These checks are required by the baseline [PWA Checklist](https://web.dev/pwa-checklist/) but are not automatically checked by Lighthouse. They do not affect your score but it's important that you verify them manually.
